summary:
The Security Council, recalling previous resolutions on the Democratic Republic of the Congo, condemns the continuing illicit flow of weapons into the country and declares its determination to monitor closely the implementation of the arms embargo.

The Council reiterates its concern regarding the presence of armed groups and militias in the eastern part of the country, which perpetuate insecurity in the region.

The Council decides to:

1. Extend until 31 March 2008 the measures on arms imposed by paragraph 20 of resolution 1493 (2003) as amended and expanded by paragraph 1 of resolution 1596 (2005);

2. Extend, for the same period, the measures on transport imposed by paragraphs 6, 7 and 10 of resolution 1596;

3. Extend, for the same period, the financial and travel measures imposed by paragraphs 13 and 15 of resolution 1596, paragraph 2 of resolution 1649 (2005), and paragraph 13 of resolution 1698 (2006);

4. Extend, for the same period, the mandate of the Group of Experts referred to in paragraph 9 of resolution 1771;

5. Remain actively seized of the matter.
